the Atlantic.

00:00:15.070 --> 00:00:16.880
ROMAN NURIK: So today's
episode is about the

00:00:16.880 --> 00:00:19.690
onboarding experience,
basically, everything from the

00:00:19.690 --> 00:00:22.530
point in which the user, you
know, downloads, maybe finds

00:00:22.530 --> 00:00:25.830
your app in the Play Store,
installs it, and then

00:00:25.830 --> 00:00:27.340
starts using it.

00:00:27.340 --> 00:00:30.260
So basically, just those kind of
initial crucial few moments

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:31.890
between the point in
which they install,

00:00:31.890 --> 00:00:33.430
and they start running.

00:00:33.430 --> 00:00:36.470
We're going to talk about ways
to make that optimal, at least

00:00:36.470 --> 00:00:39.140
as optimal as possible.

00:00:39.140 --> 00:00:40.710
NICK BUTCHER: The old saying,
you only get one chance to

00:00:40.710 --> 00:00:41.690
make a first impression.

00:00:41.690 --> 00:00:42.920
This is what this show
is all about.

00:00:42.920 --> 00:00:44.670
ROMAN NURIK: Exactly, exactly.

